# Bare Bones Basics
vim & less (run vimtutor in CLI terminal)
LFCS #1-10, #14 (tecmint LFCS)
Bash Keyboard Shortcuts (github - Bash Shortcuts)
Learn Git basics. Optionally, set up Github, Gitlab, or similar code repository system
SSL Certificates

# Set up enterprise-ready private Certificate Authority  (OpenSSL Certificate Authority - jamielinux)

Similar to "quick" CA guides, but creates persistence and organizational directories for historical storage
Use private CA to secure a live kubernetes application
K8s/CKA/CKS

Install K8s via kubeadm or, "the hard way" as linux processes (k8s.io docs)
Complete CKA Class labs. Review preceding lesson for each test not passed (kodekloud)
CKA Ultimate Practice test (killer.sh)

Take Mumshad's first on kodekloud, then transition to killer.sh (free voucher to both tests with CKA exam)
CKA Certificate

optional may as well, if you don't have yet, and can get an 80%+ on the practice
If you already have, CKS or another kube cert, while it's fresh in mind
CI/CD and automation

Install CI/CD software and create a pipeline (jenkins)
Create a terraform script to automate the linux config customizations you made throughout this guide (terraform)
SSO, SAML, OAuth

Okta Learning (learning.okta)
Set up free non-production Okta SSO instance
Integrate with kubernetes application via SAML
Scripting

sed/awk deeper dive, if not already done during LFCS (tldp micro-primer) (man -k awk)
Python (r/learnpython wiki)
Advanced Bash Scripting (tldp Bash Guide)
Programming & Development

Full-stack Web Development (Let's Go!)

Postgres/SQL
Golang
javascript
HTML/CSS
Go! Tour (go.dev)
Object-Oriented Programming

note: for non-dev paths, suggest learning C++/Java loops, then deciding whether to continue
C Programming: A Modern Approach (knking)
C++ for Programmers (Wiley)
Java (Java MOOC)
